LOCK TABLES `class_features` WRITE;
/*!40000 ALTER TABLE `class_features` DISABLE KEYS */;
INSERT INTO `class_features` VALUES (1,1,'rage','Rage',1,'In battle, you fight with primal ferocity. On your turn, you can enter a rage as a bonus action. While raging, you gain the following benefits if you aren\'t wearing heavy armor:\n- You have advantage on Strength checks and Strength saving throws.\n- When you make a melee weapon Attack using Strength, you gain a +2 bonus to the damage roll. This bonus increases as you level.\n- You have Resistance to bludgeoning, piercing, and slashing damage.\nIf you are able to cast Spells, you can\'t cast them or concentrate on them while raging.\nYour rage lasts for 1 minute. It ends early if you are knocked Unconscious or if Your Turn ends and you haven\'t attacked a hostile creature since your last turn or taken damage since then. You can also end your rage on Your Turn as a Bonus Action.\nOnce you have raged the maximum number of times for your barbarian level, you must finish a Long Rest before you can rage again. You may rage 2 times at 1st level, 3 at 3rd, 4 at 6th, 5 at 12th, and 6 at 17th.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/rage'),(2,1,'barbarian-unarmored-defense','Unarmored Defense',1,'While you are not wearing any armor, your Armor Class equals 10 + your Dexterity modifier + your Constitution modifier. You can use a shield and still gain this benefit.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/barbarian-unarmored-defense'),(3,1,'reckless-attack','Reckless Attack',2,'Starting at 2nd level, you can throw aside all concern for defense to attack with fierce desperation. When you make your first attack on your turn, you can decide to attack recklessly. Doing so gives you advantage on melee weapon attack rolls using Strength during this turn, but attack rolls against you have advantage until your next turn.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/reckless-attack'),(4,1,'danger-sense','Danger Sense',2,'At 2nd level, you gain an uncanny sense of when things nearby aren\'t as they should be, giving you an edge when you dodge away from danger. You have advantage on Dexterity saving throws against effects that you can see, such as traps and spells. To gain this benefit, you can\'t be blinded, deafened, or incapacitated.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/danger-sense'),(5,1,'primal-path','Primal Path',3,'At 3rd level, you choose a path that shapes the nature of your rage. Choose the Path of the Berserker or the Path of the Totem Warrior, both detailed at the end of the class description. Your choice grants you features at 3rd level and again at 6th, 10th, and 14th levels.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/primal-path'),(6,1,'barbarian-ability-score-improvement-1','Ability Score Improvement',4,'When you reach 4th level, and again at 8th, 12th, 16th, and 19th level, you can increase one ability score of your choice by 2, or you can increase two ability scores of your choice by 1. As normal, you can\'t increase an ability score above 20 using this feature.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/barbarian-ability-score-improvement-1'),(7,1,'barbarian-extra-attack','Extra Attack',5,'Beginning at 5th level, you can attack twice, instead of once, whenever you take the Attack action on your turn.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/barbarian-extra-attack'),(8,1,'fast-movement','Fast Movement',5,'Starting at 5th level, your speed increases by 10 feet while you aren\'t wearing heavy armor.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/fast-movement'),(9,1,'primal-path-improvement-1','Path feature',6,'At 3rd level, you choose a path that shapes the nature of your rage. Choose the Path of the Berserker or the Path of the Totem Warrior, both detailed at the end of the class description. Your choice grants you features at 3rd level and again at 6th, 10th, and 14th levels.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/primal-path-improvement-1'),(10,1,'feral-instinct','Feral Instinct',7,'By 7th level, your instincts are so honed that you have advantage on initiative rolls.\nAdditionally, if you are surprised at the beginning of combat and aren\'t incapacitated, you can act normally on your first turn, but only if you enter your rage before doing anything else on that turn.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/feral-instinct'),(11,1,'barbarian-ability-score-improvement-2','Ability Score Improvement',8,'When you reach 4th level, and again at 8th, 12th, 16th, and 19th level, you can increase one ability score of your choice by 2, or you can increase two ability scores of your choice by 1. As normal, you can\'t increase an ability score above 20 using this feature.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/barbarian-ability-score-improvement-2'),(12,1,'brutal-critical-1-die','Brutal Critical (1 die)',9,'Beginning at 9th level, you can roll one additional weapon damage die when determining the extra damage for a critical hit with a melee attack. This increases to two additional dice at 13th level and three additional dice at 17th level.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/brutal-critical-1-die'),(13,1,'primal-path-improvement-2','Path feature',10,'At 3rd level, you choose a path that shapes the nature of your rage. Choose the Path of the Berserker or the Path of the Totem Warrior, both detailed at the end of the class description. Your choice grants you features at 3rd level and again at 6th, 10th, and 14th levels.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/primal-path-improvement-2'),(14,1,'relentless-rage','Relentless Rage',11,'Starting at 11th level, your rage can keep you fighting despite grievous wounds. If you drop to 0 hit points while you\'re raging and don\'t die outright, you can make a DC 10 Constitution saving throw. If you succeed, you drop to 1 hit point instead.\nEach time you use this feature after the first, the DC increases by 5. When you finish a short or long rest, the DC resets to 10.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/relentless-rage'),(15,1,'barbarian-ability-score-improvement-3','Ability Score Improvement',12,'When you reach 4th level, and again at 8th, 12th, 16th, and 19th level, you can increase one ability score of your choice by 2, or you can increase two ability scores of your choice by 1. As normal, you can\'t increase an ability score above 20 using this feature.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/barbarian-ability-score-improvement-3'),(16,1,'brutal-critical-2-dice','Brutal Critical (2 dice)',13,'Beginning at 9th level, you can roll one additional weapon damage die when determining the extra damage for a critical hit with a melee attack. This increases to two additional dice at 13th level and three additional dice at 17th level.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/brutal-critical-2-dice'),(17,1,'primal-path-improvement-3','Path feature',14,'At 3rd level, you choose a path that shapes the nature of your rage. Choose the Path of the Berserker or the Path of the Totem Warrior, both detailed at the end of the class description. Your choice grants you features at 3rd level and again at 6th, 10th, and 14th levels.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/primal-path-improvement-3'),(18,1,'persistent-rage','Persistent Rage',15,'Beginning at 15th level, your rage is so fierce that it ends early only if you fall unconscious or if you choose to end it.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/persistent-rage'),(19,1,'barbarian-ability-score-improvement-4','Ability Score Improvement',16,'When you reach 4th level, and again at 8th, 12th, 16th, and 19th level, you can increase one ability score of your choice by 2, or you can increase two ability scores of your choice by 1. As normal, you can\'t increase an ability score above 20 using this feature.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/barbarian-ability-score-improvement-4'),(20,1,'brutal-critical-3-dice','Brutal Critical (3 dice)',17,'Beginning at 9th level, you can roll one additional weapon damage die when determining the extra damage for a critical hit with a melee attack. This increases to two additional dice at 13th level and three additional dice at 17th level.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/brutal-critical-3-dice'),(21,1,'indomitable-might','Indomitable Might',18,'Beginning at 18th level, if your total for a Strength check is less than your Strength score, you can use that score in place of the total.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/indomitable-might'),(22,1,'barbarian-ability-score-improvement-5','Ability Score Improvement',19,'When you reach 4th level, and again at 8th, 12th, 16th, and 19th level, you can increase one ability score of your choice by 2, or you can increase two ability scores of your choice by 1. As normal, you can\'t increase an ability score above 20 using this feature.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/barbarian-ability-score-improvement-5'),(23,1,'primal-champion','Primal Champion',20,'At 20th level, you embody the power of the wilds. Your Strength and Constitution scores increase by 4. Your maximum for those scores is now 24.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/primal-champion'),(24,2,'spellcasting-bard','Spellcasting: Bard',1,'You have learned to untangle and reshape the fabric of reality in harmony with your wishes and music. Your spells are part of your vast repertoire, magic that you can tune to different situations.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/spellcasting-bard'),(25,2,'bardic-inspiration-d6','Bardic Inspiration (d6)',1,'You can inspire others through stirring words or music. To do so, you use a bonus action on your turn to choose one creature other than yourself within 60 feet of you who can hear you. That creature gains one Bardic Inspiration die, a d6. Once within the next 10 minutes, the creature can roll the die and add the number rolled to one ability check, attack roll, or saving throw it makes. The creature can wait until after it rolls the d20 before deciding to use the Bardic Inspiration die, but must decide before the GM says whether the roll succeeds or fails. Once the Bardic Inspiration die is rolled, it is lost. A creature can have only one Bardic Inspiration die at a time.\nYou can use this feature a number of times equal to your Charisma modifier (a minimum of once). You regain any expended uses when you finish a long rest. \nYour Bardic Inspiration die changes when you reach certain levels in this class. The die becomes a d8 at 5th level, a d10 at 10th level, and a d12 at 15th level.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/bardic-inspiration-d6'),(26,2,'jack-of-all-trades','Jack of All Trades',2,'Starting at 2nd level, you can add half your proficiency bonus, rounded down, to any ability check you make that doesn\'t already include your proficiency bonus.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/jack-of-all-trades'),(27,2,'song-of-rest-d6','Song of Rest (d6)',2,'Beginning at 2nd level, you can use soothing music or oration to help revitalize your wounded allies during a short rest. If you or any friendly creatures who can hear your performance regain hit points at the end of the short rest by spending one or more Hit Dice, each of those creatures regains an extra 1d6 hit points. \nThe extra hit points increase when you reach certain levels in this class: to 1d8 at 9th level, to 1d10 at 13th level, and to 1d12 at 17th level.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/song-of-rest-d6'),(28,2,'bard-expertise-1','Expertise',3,'At 3rd level, choose two of your skill proficiencies. Your proficiency bonus is doubled for any ability check you make that uses either of the chosen proficiencies. At 10th level, you can choose another two skill proficiencies to gain this benefit.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/bard-expertise-1'),(29,2,'bard-college','Bard College',3,'At 3rd level, you delve into the advanced techniques of a bard college of your choice, such as the College of Lore. Your choice grants you features at 3rd level and again at 6th and 14th level.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/bard-college'),(30,2,'bard-ability-score-improvement-1','Ability Score Improvement',4,'When you reach 4th level, and again at 8th, 12th, 16th, and 19th level, you can increase one ability score of your choice by 2, or you can increase two ability scores of your choice by 1. As normal, you can\'t increase an ability score above 20 using this feature.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/bard-ability-score-improvement-1'),(31,2,'bardic-inspiration-d8','Bardic Inspiration (d8)',5,'You can inspire others through stirring words or music. To do so, you use a bonus action on your turn to choose one creature other than yourself within 60 feet of you who can hear you. That creature gains one Bardic Inspiration die, a d6. Once within the next 10 minutes, the creature can roll the die and add the number rolled to one ability check, attack roll, or saving throw it makes. The creature can wait until after it rolls the d20 before deciding to use the Bardic Inspiration die, but must decide before the GM says whether the roll succeeds or fails. Once the Bardic Inspiration die is rolled, it is lost. A creature can have only one Bardic Inspiration die at a time.\nYou can use this feature a number of times equal to your Charisma modifier (a minimum of once). You regain any expended uses when you finish a long rest. \nYour Bardic Inspiration die changes when you reach certain levels in this class. The die becomes a d8 at 5th level, a d10 at 10th level, and a d12 at 15th level.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/bardic-inspiration-d8'),(32,2,'font-of-inspiration','Font of Inspiration',5,'Beginning when you reach 5th level, you regain all of your expended uses of Bardic Inspiration when you finish a short or long rest.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/font-of-inspiration'),(33,2,'countercharm','Countercharm',6,'At 6th level, you gain the ability to use musical notes or words of power to disrupt mind-influencing effects. As an action, you can start a performance that lasts until the end of your next turn. During that time, you and any friendly creatures within 30 feet of you have advantage on saving throws against being frightened or charmed. A creature must be able to hear you to gain this benefit. The performance ends early if you are incapacitated or silenced or if you voluntarily end it (no action required).','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/countercharm'),(34,2,'bard-college-improvement-1','Bard College feature',6,'At 3rd level, you delve into the advanced techniques of a bard college of your choice, such as the College of Lore. Your choice grants you features at 3rd level and again at 6th and 14th level.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/bard-college-improvement-1'),(35,2,'bard-ability-score-improvement-2','Ability Score Improvement',8,'When you reach 4th level, and again at 8th, 12th, 16th, and 19th level, you can increase one ability score of your choice by 2, or you can increase two ability scores of your choice by 1. As normal, you can\'t increase an ability score above 20 using this feature.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/bard-ability-score-improvement-2'),(36,2,'song-of-rest-d8','Song of Rest (d8)',9,'Beginning at 2nd level, you can use soothing music or oration to help revitalize your wounded allies during a short rest. If you or any friendly creatures who can hear your performance regain hit points at the end of the short rest by spending one or more Hit Dice, each of those creatures regains an extra 1d6 hit points. \nThe extra hit points increase when you reach certain levels in this class: to 1d8 at 9th level, to 1d10 at 13th level, and to 1d12 at 17th level.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/song-of-rest-d8'),(37,2,'bard-expertise-2','Expertise',10,'At 3rd level, choose two of your skill proficiencies. Your proficiency bonus is doubled for any ability check you make that uses either of the chosen proficiencies. At 10th level, you can choose another two skill proficiencies to gain this benefit.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/bard-expertise-2'),(38,2,'bardic-inspiration-d10','Bardic Inspiration (d10)',10,'You can inspire others through stirring words or music. To do so, you use a bonus action on your turn to choose one creature other than yourself within 60 feet of you who can hear you. That creature gains one Bardic Inspiration die, a d6. Once within the next 10 minutes, the creature can roll the die and add the number rolled to one ability check, attack roll, or saving throw it makes. The creature can wait until after it rolls the d20 before deciding to use the Bardic Inspiration die, but must decide before the GM says whether the roll succeeds or fails. Once the Bardic Inspiration die is rolled, it is lost. A creature can have only one Bardic Inspiration die at a time.\nYou can use this feature a number of times equal to your Charisma modifier (a minimum of once). You regain any expended uses when you finish a long rest. \nYour Bardic Inspiration die changes when you reach certain levels in this class. The die becomes a d8 at 5th level, a d10 at 10th level, and a d12 at 15th level.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/bardic-inspiration-d10'),(39,2,'magical-secrets-1','Magical Secrets',10,'By 10th level, you have plundered magical knowledge from a wide spectrum of disciplines. Choose two spells from any class, including this one. A spell you choose must be of a level you can cast, as shown on the Bard table, or a cantrip. \nThe chosen spells count as bard spells for you and are included in the number in the Spells Known column of the Bard table. \nYou learn two additional spells from any class at 14th level and again at 18th level.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/magical-secrets-1'),(40,2,'bard-ability-score-improvement-3','Ability Score Improvement',12,'When you reach 4th level, and again at 8th, 12th, 16th, and 19th level, you can increase one ability score of your choice by 2, or you can increase two ability scores of your choice by 1. As normal, you can\'t increase an ability score above 20 using this feature.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/bard-ability-score-improvement-3'),(41,2,'song-of-rest-d10','Song of Rest (d10)',13,'Beginning at 2nd level, you can use soothing music or oration to help revitalize your wounded allies during a short rest. If you or any friendly creatures who can hear your performance regain hit points at the end of the short rest by spending one or more Hit Dice, each of those creatures regains an extra 1d6 hit points. \nThe extra hit points increase when you reach certain levels in this class: to 1d8 at 9th level, to 1d10 at 13th level, and to 1d12 at 17th level.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/song-of-rest-d10'),(42,2,'magical-secrets-2','Magical Secrets',14,'By 10th level, you have plundered magical knowledge from a wide spectrum of disciplines. Choose two spells from any class, including this one. A spell you choose must be of a level you can cast, as shown on the Bard table, or a cantrip. \nThe chosen spells count as bard spells for you and are included in the number in the Spells Known column of the Bard table. \nYou learn two additional spells from any class at 14th level and again at 18th level.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/magical-secrets-2'),(43,2,'bard-college-improvement-2','Bard College feature',14,'At 3rd level, you delve into the advanced techniques of a bard college of your choice, such as the College of Lore. Your choice grants you features at 3rd level and again at 6th and 14th level.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/bard-college-improvement-2'),(44,2,'bardic-inspiration-d12','Bardic Inspiration (d12)',15,'You can inspire others through stirring words or music. To do so, you use a bonus action on your turn to choose one creature other than yourself within 60 feet of you who can hear you. That creature gains one Bardic Inspiration die, a d6. Once within the next 10 minutes, the creature can roll the die and add the number rolled to one ability check, attack roll, or saving throw it makes. The creature can wait until after it rolls the d20 before deciding to use the Bardic Inspiration die, but must decide before the GM says whether the roll succeeds or fails. Once the Bardic Inspiration die is rolled, it is lost. A creature can have only one Bardic Inspiration die at a time.\nYou can use this feature a number of times equal to your Charisma modifier (a minimum of once). You regain any expended uses when you finish a long rest. \nYour Bardic Inspiration die changes when you reach certain levels in this class. The die becomes a d8 at 5th level, a d10 at 10th level, and a d12 at 15th level.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/bardic-inspiration-d12'),(45,2,'bard-ability-score-improvement-4','Ability Score Improvement',16,'When you reach 4th level, and again at 8th, 12th, 16th, and 19th level, you can increase one ability score of your choice by 2, or you can increase two ability scores of your choice by 1. As normal, you can\'t increase an ability score above 20 using this feature.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/bard-ability-score-improvement-4'),(46,2,'song-of-rest-d12','Song of Rest (d12)',17,'Beginning at 2nd level, you can use soothing music or oration to help revitalize your wounded allies during a short rest. If you or any friendly creatures who can hear your performance regain hit points at the end of the short rest by spending one or more Hit Dice, each of those creatures regains an extra 1d6 hit points. \nThe extra hit points increase when you reach certain levels in this class: to 1d8 at 9th level, to 1d10 at 13th level, and to 1d12 at 17th level.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/song-of-rest-d12'),(47,2,'magical-secrets-3','Magical Secrets',18,'By 10th level, you have plundered magical knowledge from a wide spectrum of disciplines. Choose two spells from any class, including this one. A spell you choose must be of a level you can cast, as shown on the Bard table, or a cantrip. \nThe chosen spells count as bard spells for you and are included in the number in the Spells Known column of the Bard table. \nYou learn two additional spells from any class at 14th level and again at 18th level.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/magical-secrets-3'),(48,2,'bard-ability-score-improvement-5','Ability Score Improvement',19,'When you reach 4th level, and again at 8th, 12th, 16th, and 19th level, you can increase one ability score of your choice by 2, or you can increase two ability scores of your choice by 1. As normal, you can\'t increase an ability score above 20 using this feature.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/bard-ability-score-improvement-5'),(49,2,'superior-inspiration','Superior Inspiration',20,'At 20th level, when you roll initiative and have no uses of Bardic Inspiration left, you regain one use.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/superior-inspiration'),(50,3,'spellcasting-cleric','Spellcasting: Cleric',1,'As a conduit for divine power, you can cast cleric spells.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/spellcasting-cleric'),(51,3,'divine-domain','Divine Domain',1,'Choose one domain related to your deity, such as Knowledge, Life, Light, Nature, Tempest, Trickery, or War. Only the Life domain is detailed in the Open Game Licensed SRD. Additional Domains are described in the official rulebooks or products from other publishers.\nYour domain grants you domain spells and other features when you choose it at 1st level. It also grants you additional ways to use Channel Divinity when you gain that feature at 2nd level, and additional benefits at 6th, 8th, and 17th levels.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/divine-domain'),(52,3,'domain-spells-1','Domain Spells',1,'Each domain has a list of spells--its domain spells--that you gain at the cleric levels noted in the domain description. Once you gain a domain spell, you always have it prepared, and it doesn\'t count against the number of spells you can prepare each day.\nIf you have a domain spell that doesn\'t appear on the cleric spell list, the spell is nonetheless a cleric spell for you.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/domain-spells-1'),(53,3,'channel-divinity-1-rest','Channel Divinity (1/rest)',2,'At 2nd level, you gain the ability to channel divine energy directly from your deity, using that energy to fuel magical effects. You start with two such effects: Turn Undead and an effect determined by your domain. Some domains grant you additional effects as you advance in levels, as noted in the domain description.\nWhen you use your Channel Divinity, you choose which effect to create. You must then finish a short or long rest to use your Channel Divinity again.\nSome Channel Divinity effects require saving throws. When you use such an effect from this class, the DC equals your cleric spell save DC.\nBeginning at 6th level, you can use your Channel Divinity twice between rests, and beginning at 18th level, you can use it three times between rests. When you finish a short or long rest, you regain your expended uses.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/channel-divinity-1-rest'),(54,3,'channel-divinity-turn-undead','Channel Divinity: Turn Undead',2,'As an action, you present your holy symbol and speak a prayer censuring the undead. Each undead that can see or hear you within 30 feet of you must make a Wisdom saving throw. If the creature fails its saving throw, it is turned for 1 minute or until it takes any damage.\nA turned creature must spend its turns trying to move as far away from you as it can, and it can\'t willingly move to a space within 30 feet of you. It also can\'t take reactions. For its action, it can use only the Dash action or try to escape from an effect that prevents it from moving. If there\'s nowhere to move, the creature can use the Dodge action.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/channel-divinity-turn-undead'),(55,3,'divine-domain-improvement-1','Divine Domain feature',2,'Choose one domain related to your deity, such as Knowledge, Life, Light, Nature, Tempest, Trickery, or War. Only the Life domain is detailed in the Open Game Licensed SRD. Additional Domains are described in the official rulebooks or products from other publishers.\nYour domain grants you domain spells and other features when you choose it at 1st level. It also grants you additional ways to use Channel Divinity when you gain that feature at 2nd level, and additional benefits at 6th, 8th, and 17th levels.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/divine-domain-improvement-1'),(56,3,'domain-spells-2','Domain Spells',3,'Each domain has a list of spells--its domain spells--that you gain at the cleric levels noted in the domain description. Once you gain a domain spell, you always have it prepared, and it doesn\'t count against the number of spells you can prepare each day.\nIf you have a domain spell that doesn\'t appear on the cleric spell list, the spell is nonetheless a cleric spell for you.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/domain-spells-2'),(57,3,'cleric-ability-score-improvement-1','Ability Score Improvement',4,'When you reach 4th level, and again at 8th, 12th, 16th, and 19th level, you can increase one ability score of your choice by 2, or you can increase two ability scores of your choice by 1. As normal, you can\'t increase an ability score above 20 using this feature.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/cleric-ability-score-improvement-1'),(58,3,'domain-spells-3','Domain Spells',5,'Each domain has a list of spells--its domain spells--that you gain at the cleric levels noted in the domain description. Once you gain a domain spell, you always have it prepared, and it doesn\'t count against the number of spells you can prepare each day.\nIf you have a domain spell that doesn\'t appear on the cleric spell list, the spell is nonetheless a cleric spell for you.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/domain-spells-3'),(59,3,'destroy-undead-cr-1-2-or-below','Destroy Undead (CR 1/2 or below)',5,'Starting at 5th level, when an undead fails its saving throw against your Turn Undead feature, the creature is instantly destroyed if its challenge rating is at or below a certain threshold.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/destroy-undead-cr-1-2-or-below'),(60,3,'channel-divinity-2-rest','Channel Divinity (2/rest)',6,'Beginning at 6th level, you can use your Channel Divinity twice between rests, and beginning at 18th level, you can use it three times between rests. When you finish a short or long rest, you regain your expended uses.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/channel-divinity-2-rest'),(61,3,'divine-domain-improvement-2','Divine Domain feature',6,'Choose one domain related to your deity, such as Knowledge, Life, Light, Nature, Tempest, Trickery, or War. Only the Life domain is detailed in the Open Game Licensed SRD. Additional Domains are described in the official rulebooks or products from other publishers.\nYour domain grants you domain spells and other features when you choose it at 1st level. It also grants you additional ways to use Channel Divinity when you gain that feature at 2nd level, and additional benefits at 6th, 8th, and 17th levels.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/divine-domain-improvement-2'),(62,3,'domain-spells-4','Domain Spells',7,'Each domain has a list of spells--its domain spells--that you gain at the cleric levels noted in the domain description. Once you gain a domain spell, you always have it prepared, and it doesn\'t count against the number of spells you can prepare each day.\nIf you have a domain spell that doesn\'t appear on the cleric spell list, the spell is nonetheless a cleric spell for you.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/domain-spells-4'),(63,3,'cleric-ability-score-improvement-2','Ability Score Improvement',8,'When you reach 4th level, and again at 8th, 12th, 16th, and 19th level, you can increase one ability score of your choice by 2, or you can increase two ability scores of your choice by 1. As normal, you can\'t increase an ability score above 20 using this feature.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/cleric-ability-score-improvement-2'),(64,3,'destroy-undead-cr-1-or-below','Destroy Undead (CR 1 or below)',8,'Starting at 5th level, when an undead fails its saving throw against your Turn Undead feature, the creature is instantly destroyed if its challenge rating is at or below a certain threshold.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/destroy-undead-cr-1-or-below'),(65,3,'divine-domain-improvement-3','Divine Domain feature',8,'Choose one domain related to your deity, such as Knowledge, Life, Light, Nature, Tempest, Trickery, or War. Only the Life domain is detailed in the Open Game Licensed SRD. Additional Domains are described in the official rulebooks or products from other publishers.\nYour domain grants you domain spells and other features when you choose it at 1st level. It also grants you additional ways to use Channel Divinity when you gain that feature at 2nd level, and additional benefits at 6th, 8th, and 17th levels.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/divine-domain-improvement-3'),(66,3,'domain-spells-5','Domain Spells',9,'Each domain has a list of spells--its domain spells--that you gain at the cleric levels noted in the domain description. Once you gain a domain spell, you always have it prepared, and it doesn\'t count against the number of spells you can prepare each day.\nIf you have a domain spell that doesn\'t appear on the cleric spell list, the spell is nonetheless a cleric spell for you.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/domain-spells-5'),(67,3,'divine-intervention','Divine Intervention',10,'Beginning at 10th level, you can call on your deity to intervene on your behalf when your need is great.\nImploring your deity\'s aid requires you to use your action. Describe the assistance you seek, and roll percentile dice. If you roll a number equal to or lower than your cleric level, your deity intervenes. The GM chooses the nature of the intervention; the effect of any cleric spell or cleric domain spell would be appropriate.\nIf your deity intervenes, you can\'t use this feature again for 7 days. Otherwise, you can use it again after you finish a long rest.\nAt 20th level, your call for intervention succeeds automatically, no roll required.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/divine-intervention'),(68,3,'destroy-undead-cr-2-or-below','Destroy Undead (CR 2 or below)',11,'Starting at 5th level, when an undead fails its saving throw against your Turn Undead feature, the creature is instantly destroyed if its challenge rating is at or below a certain threshold.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/destroy-undead-cr-2-or-below'),(69,3,'cleric-ability-score-improvement-3','Ability Score Improvement',12,'When you reach 4th level, and again at 8th, 12th, 16th, and 19th level, you can increase one ability score of your choice by 2, or you can increase two ability scores of your choice by 1. As normal, you can\'t increase an ability score above 20 using this feature.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/cleric-ability-score-improvement-3'),(70,3,'destroy-undead-cr-3-or-below','Destroy Undead (CR 3 or below)',14,'Starting at 5th level, when an undead fails its saving throw against your Turn Undead feature, the creature is instantly destroyed if its challenge rating is at or below a certain threshold.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/destroy-undead-cr-3-or-below'),(71,3,'cleric-ability-score-improvement-4','Ability Score Improvement',16,'When you reach 4th level, and again at 8th, 12th, 16th, and 19th level, you can increase one ability score of your choice by 2, or you can increase two ability scores of your choice by 1. As normal, you can\'t increase an ability score above 20 using this feature.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/cleric-ability-score-improvement-4'),(72,3,'destroy-undead-cr-4-or-below','Destroy Undead (CR 4 or below)',17,'Starting at 5th level, when an undead fails its saving throw against your Turn Undead feature, the creature is instantly destroyed if its challenge rating is at or below a certain threshold.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/destroy-undead-cr-4-or-below'),(73,3,'divine-domain-improvement-4','Divine Domain feature',17,'Choose one domain related to your deity, such as Knowledge, Life, Light, Nature, Tempest, Trickery, or War. Only the Life domain is detailed in the Open Game Licensed SRD. Additional Domains are described in the official rulebooks or products from other publishers.\nYour domain grants you domain spells and other features when you choose it at 1st level. It also grants you additional ways to use Channel Divinity when you gain that feature at 2nd level, and additional benefits at 6th, 8th, and 17th levels.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/divine-domain-improvement-4'),(74,3,'channel-divinity-3-rest','Channel Divinity (3/rest)',18,'Beginning at 6th level, you can use your Channel Divinity twice between rests, and beginning at 18th level, you can use it three times between rests. When you finish a short or long rest, you regain your expended uses.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/channel-divinity-3-rest'),(75,3,'cleric-ability-score-improvement-5','Ability Score Improvement',19,'When you reach 4th level, and again at 8th, 12th, 16th, and 19th level, you can increase one ability score of your choice by 2, or you can increase two ability scores of your choice by 1. As normal, you can\'t increase an ability score above 20 using this feature.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/cleric-ability-score-improvement-5'),(76,3,'divine-intervention-improvement','Divine Intervention Improvement',20,'At 20th level, your call for intervention succeeds automatically, no roll required.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/divine-intervention-improvement'),(77,4,'spellcasting-druid','Spellcasting: Druid',1,'Drawing on the divine essence of nature itself, you can cast spells to shape that essence to your will.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/spellcasting-druid'),(78,4,'druidic','Druidic',1,'You know Druidic, the secret language of druids. You can speak the language and use it to leave hidden messages. You and others who know this language automatically spot such a message. Others spot the message\'s presence with a successful DC 15 Wisdom (Perception) check but can\'t decipher it without magic.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/druidic'),(79,4,'wild-shape-cr-1-4-or-below-no-flying-or-swim-speed','Wild Shape (CR 1/4 or below, no flying or swim speed)',2,'Starting at 2nd level, you can use your action to magically assume the shape of a beast that you have seen before. You can use this feature twice. You regain expended uses when you finish a short or long rest.\nYour druid level determines the beasts you can transform into, as shown in the Beast Shapes table. At 2nd level, for example, you can transform into any beast that has a challenge rating of 1/4 or lower that doesn\'t have a flying or swimming speed.\nYou can stay in a beast shape for a number of hours equal to half your druid level (rounded down). You then revert to your normal form unless you expend another use of this feature. You can revert to your normal form earlier by using a bonus action on your turn. You automatically revert if you fall unconscious, drop to 0 hit points, or die.\nWhile you are transformed, the following rules apply:\n- Your game statistics are replaced by the statistics of the beast, but you retain your alignment, personality, and Intelligence, Wisdom, and Charisma scores. You also retain all of your skill and saving throw proficiencies, in addition to gaining those of the creature. If the creature has the same proficiency as you and the bonus in its stat block is higher than yours, use the creature\'s bonus instead of yours. If the creature has any legendary or lair actions, you can\'t use them.\n- When you transform, you assume the beast\'s hit points and Hit Dice. When you revert to your normal form, you return to the number of hit points you had before you transformed. However, if you revert as a result of dropping to 0 hit points, any excess damage carries over to your normal form. For example, if you take 10 damage in animal form and have only 1 hit point left, you revert and take 9 damage. As long as the excess damage doesn\'t reduce your normal form to 0 hit points, you aren\'t knocked unconscious.\n- You can\'t cast spells, and your ability to speak or take any action that requires hands is limited to the capabilities of your beast form. Transforming doesn\'t break your concentration on a spell you\'ve already cast, however, or prevent you from taking actions that are part of a spell, such as call lightning, that you\'ve already cast.\n- You retain the benefit of any features from your class, race, or other source and can use them if the new form is physically capable of doing so. However, you can\'t use any of your special senses, such as darkvision, unless your new form also has that sense.\n- You choose whether your equipment falls to the ground in your space, merges into your new form, or is worn by it. Worn equipment functions as normal, but the GM decides whether it is practical for the new form to wear a piece of equipment, based on the creature\'s shape and size. Your equipment doesn\'t change size or shape to match the new form, and any equipment that the new form can\'t wear must either fall to the ground or merge with it. Equipment that merges with the form has no effect until you leave the form.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/wild-shape-cr-1-4-or-below-no-flying-or-swim-speed'),(80,4,'druid-circle','Druid Circle',2,'At 2nd level, you choose to identify with a circle of druids, such as the Circle of the Land. Your choice grants you features at 2nd level and again at 6th, 10th, and 14th level.','https://www.dnd5eapi.co/api/2014/features/druid-circle'),(81,4,'wild-shape-cr-1-2-or-below-no-flying-speed','Wild Shape (CR 1/2 or below, no flying speed)',4,'Starting at 2nd level, you can use your action to magically assume the shape of a beast that you have seen before. You can use this feature twice. You regain expended uses when you finish a short or long rest.\nYour druid level determines the beasts you can transform into, as shown in the Beast Shapes table. At 2nd level, for example, you can transform into any beast that has a challenge rating of 1/4 or lower that doesn\'t have a flying or swimming speed.\nYou can stay in a beast shape for a number of hours equal to half your druid level (rounded down). You then revert to your normal form unless you expend another use of this feature. You can revert to your normal form earlier by using a bonus action on your turn. You automatically revert if you fall unconscious, drop to 0 hit points, or die.\nWhile you are transformed, the following rules apply:\n- Your game statistics are replaced by the statistics of the beast, but you retain your alignment, personality, and Intelligence, Wisdom, and Charisma scores. You also retain all of your skill and saving throw proficiencies, in addition to gaining those of the creature. If the creature has the same proficiency as you and the bonus in its stat block is higher than yours, use the creature\'s bonus instead of yours. If the creature has any legendary or lair actions, you can\'t use them.\n- When you transform, you assume the beast\'s hit points and Hit Dice. When you revert to your normal form, you return to the number of hit points you had before you transformed. However, if you revert as a result of dropping to 0 hit points, any excess damage carries over to your normal form. For examp